  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nCLI ergonomics could be improved by renaming `--slots-per-restore-point` to `--restore-points-per-historical-batch` and making it take only power of two arguments.  That way, higher value corresponds to more disk space consumed, and conversely, lower value to less disk space.  So the two are correlated.  Currently, with `--slots-per-restore-point`, there's negative correlation and the option is harder to parse mentally.",
